Get a parsed version of the API response for a data set's meta data

get_meta.Rd

Get a list of metadata information for a data set available from the EES API. Provides either look-up tables from human readable labels to ids used in the API, or the raw response from the meta endpoint.

Usage

get_meta(
  dataset_id,
  dataset_version = NULL,
  preview_token = NULL,
  ees_environment = NULL,
  api_version = NULL,
  verbose = FALSE
)

Arguments

dataset_id

ID of data set to be connected to. This is required if the endpoint is one of "get-dataset-versions", "get-summary", "get-meta", "get-csv", "get-data" or "post-data"

dataset_version

Version of data set to be connected to

preview_token

Preview token required for access to private data sets

ees_environment

EES ees_environment to connect to: "dev", "test", "preprod" or "prod"

api_version

EES API version

verbose

Run with additional contextual messaging. Logical, default = FALSE

Value

List of data frames containing a data set's meta data

get_meta(example_id())
